# no-hardcoded-paths.allow — intentional <file>:<line> exceptions to the
# no-hardcoded-paths linter (see scripts/lint/no-hardcoded-paths.sh).
#
# Format: one <path>:<line> per line, relative to repo root. Comments allowed
# (lines starting with #), blank lines ignored. Matching is prefix-based on
# the grep output's "<file>:<line>:" stem.
#
# Adding an entry here is a deliberate signal that the maintainer-path or
# brand mention at that location is intentional prose (teaching example,
# documentation reference, etc.) — not a regression. Allowlisting should
# be the exception, not the default: prefer rewording the offending line
# whenever the meaning can be preserved with a generic placeholder.
#
# When adding: include a short comment above the entry explaining WHY the
# mention is intentional, so future-you (or another reviewer) can verify
# the exception still makes sense if the file is later restructured.

